social_posts.post_text: In 2009 I moved from New York to Miami without a plan- I just had an instinct that it was what I should do. I found Coco about a month later and met my partner the same day. This magical dog knew all the people I love most in my life. I think she had a happy life with us, despite the fact that she once tried to run off with a handsome dog named Brutus (@sophiesparis @lausass @lolosilvera) in Haiti. She died in our arms on Saturday night and I think I will feel her absence for the rest of my life. 💔❤️

I had the pleasure of photographing jazz singer Paula West @mspaulawest for the New Yorker last week. The photograph illustrates a lovely tribute to the West’s album “Temptation” written by Nathan Heller.

One of the highlights of this year was being able to spend time with Haitians in the Dominican Republic while working with @projecthope. Meeting this little girl and her family was one of the many things that I am grateful for this year.
Many years ago on top of the Hotel Deauville in Havana.
Sylvio Cator Stadium, Port-au-Prince on the one year earthquake anniversary. January 12, 2011 #🇭🇹
Adventuring with the children of people you have had great adventures with is a beautiful experience.
From the archives. Years ago in the mountains of Haiti. #🐇 #🇭🇹 ❤️

Missing this magical dog who left us in December. I started a new account @luckyhumanphotos a few months ago as way to heal from this loss and also as a place to think about the roles that pets play in our lives. #lavieseboul

During this very challenging but somehow still beautiful year I have been using photography therapeutically to heal and grow. Inspired by reading, education and teachings from Francesca Belgiojoso @photography_in_therapy one of the ways that I have used photography to heal has been to engage with pictures of myself. #therapeuticphotography #arttherapy
I have been editing and organizing old Haiti work- an emotional experience. I have found a series of collages that I didn’t really know that I had. Here is one made about the market at Pont-Sondé. 🇭🇹

An ode to the Zenaida, or turtle dove of the Leeward Islands. I made this in the spring as a tribute to this bird that appears periodically in my dreams. I made the bird while learning the raku process and was inspired by Haitian artist Marithou Dupoux. #zenaidadove #turtledove #raku #marithoudupoux

These two photos were made in Poland over the summer while working for @projecthope. While in the region I heard the stories  of many Ukrainians who were forced to leave their county. Project HOPE supports local partners who provide mental health support to those displaced by the war. 

Tetiana, pictured above lives in a safe house in Poland and waits for news from her son who is fighting in the war. Among the 6 million Ukrainians who have fled their country, many are seniors who were forced to leave everything behind.

The next image was made in a center for children during an art therapy session. The drawing was made by a little girl who was unable to bring her cat with her when she was forced to flee her country.

A woman holding a picture of her husband who was killed during the 2010 earthquake at a memorial in Port-au-Prince many years ago. Today is the anniversary of the earthquake that took the lives of an incomprehensible number of people 14 years ago. Love to Haiti today and always. 🇭🇹

It was a pleasure and an honor to work with @corrinebotz @catjimenez and @alexmediate at @youngarts this past week. Eleven talented high school aged photographers who were selected as Winners with Distinction traveled to Miami for National Young Arts week. I am inspired by the talent, intelligence, insight and empathy we witnessed from these young artists this past week and look forward to seeing what they create in the future.
The amazing list of guest artists included  Elinor Carucci, Mickalene Thomas, Anastasia Samoylova, Clara Toro, Eric Gottesman, Laurie Simmons and Sorcha Augustine. 
Thank you to the team @youngarts that makes it all happen! 
What an inspirational beginning to 2024! 
#youngarts
